HEADWORD: Colophene
<hw>Co"lo*phene</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless, oily liquid, formerly obtained by
distillation of colophony. It is regarded as a polymeric form of
terebenthene. Called also <altname>diterebene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

